# Railway Environment Variables Template
# Copy this to your Railway project's environment variables

# ===========================================
# RAILWAY BUILT-IN DATABASE (PostgreSQL)
# ===========================================
# These will be automatically provided by Railway when you add a PostgreSQL database
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@containers-us-west-1.railway.app:1234/railway
# DATABASE_HOST=containers-us-west-1.railway.app
# DATABASE_PORT=1234
# DATABASE_NAME=railway
# DATABASE_USER=postgres
# DATABASE_PASSWORD=password

# ===========================================
# BACKEND CONFIGURATION
# ===========================================

# Server Configuration
SERVER_HOST=0.0.0.0
SERVER_PORT=8080

# Database (will be provided by Railway PostgreSQL)
DB_SSLMODE=require

# JWT Configuration (REQUIRED - Generate a secure random string!)
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production-32-chars-minimum

# Storage Configuration
STORAGE_PATH=./uploads

# Environment
GIN_MODE=release
LOG_LEVEL=info

# ===========================================
# FRONTEND CONFIGURATION
# ===========================================

# API Configuration (will be the backend service URL)
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-service.railway.app
# Or use Railway's internal networking:
# VITE_API_URL=http://backend:8080

# ===========================================
# RAILWAY SPECIFIC
# ===========================================

# Railway provides these automatically:
# RAILWAY_PROJECT_ID
# RAILWAY_ENVIRONMENT_ID
# RAILWAY_SERVICE_ID
# RAILWAY_SERVICE_NAME
# RAILWAY_PROJECT_NAME
# RAILWAY_ENVIRONMENT_NAME

# ===========================================
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# ===========================================

# 1. Create a new Railway project
# 2. Add PostgreSQL database (Railway will provide DATABASE_* variables)
# 3. Deploy backend service first
# 4. Get backend URL and set VITE_API_URL for frontend
# 5. Deploy frontend service
# 6. Configure domains if needed

# Security Checklist for Railway:
# ✅ Set a strong JWT_SECRET (64+ characters)
# ✅ Use Railway's built-in PostgreSQL
# ✅ Enable Railway's health checks
# ✅ Configure proper CORS in production
# ✅ Set up Railway's backup features
